

One U.S. soldier was killed in a small arms fire in Baghdad on Tuesday, the U.S. military said Thursday in a statement.

According to the statement, the latest killing bring the number of U.S. soldiers killed on Tuesday to seven.

Late on Wednesday the military said that two U.S. soldiers were killed at approximately 11:30 p.m. (0830 GMT) on Tuesday when their vehicle was struck by a roadside bomb in northwest of Baghdad.

Before that, four more soldiers, including three marines, were killed in Iraq's western Anbar province, said the military.

Since the U.S.-led war in Iraq broke out in March 2003, more than 2,850 U.S. soldiers have been killed in the war-torn country, according to media count.

